# AWS EC2 Pricing

With AWS EC2 you pay for the compute time. You only pay for the compute time that you use. It offers different pricing options.

| **Pricing Option**          | **Description**                                                                                                                                               | **Best Used For**                                                                                                                |
|-----------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **On Demand Instances**     | On Demand Instances are best used for short-term workloads. It requires no upfront costs or minimum amount on the purchase. The instances run until you stop them. You pay for what you use. | Short-term workloads without upfront costs or long-term commitment.                                                              |
| **AWS EC2 Savings Plan**    | The savings plan is a commitment for usage over a 1-year or 3-year term. Committing to a period gives a discounted price. If you surpass the budget, the cost goes to normal (on-demand) prices. | Long-term commitment with cost savings.                                                                                          |
| **Reserved Instances**      | The Reserved Instances are used to reserve instances for an agreed period. The options are for 1-year or 3-years. The latter one gives the highest discount.    | Long-term, predictable workloads where you can commit to using EC2 for a 1-year or 3-year period.                                 |
| **Spot Instances**          | This pricing model is best for workloads with flexible start and end times, which can take interruptions. Spot instances can give up to a 90% cost savings. The reason behind the discount is that AWS can optimize its capacity, giving you better prices. | Workloads that can handle interruptions and have flexible start and end times, benefiting from significant cost savings.          |
| **Dedicated Hosts**         | Dedicated hosts are physical servers fully dedicated to you. You can use your existing VM software licenses. The Dedicated Host is the most expensive model.    | Workloads requiring physical isolation and the ability to use existing VM software licenses, despite the higher cost.             |
